<p>I am trying to apply in <code>ggplot2</code> the "Set1" palette from <code>rcolorbrewer</code> for line charts so the colours match that for bar charts using the same colour palette.  The following is what works for the bar charts:</p>  <pre><code>ggplot(region, aes(Year, Em_sum, fill=Region, order=Region)) +      geom_bar(stat='identity') + scale_fill_brewer(palette="Set1") +      guides(fill = guide_legend(reverse=T)) + scale_y_continuous(labels = comma) +     ylab("Emissions (kt)") +     theme_bw(base_size=20, base_family='Helvetica') +     theme(legend.position = c(0.2, 0.8), legend.background = element_rect(colour = "black")) +     scale_x_discrete(breaks=seq(1961, 2011, 10)) </code></pre>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/qca3D.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/qca3D.png" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>  <p>Using <code>geom_line()</code> instead of <code>geom_bar()</code> produces a very different colour palette for the Regions.  I have also tried to manually set the colour paletter equal to Set1 as follows, but without success.</p>  <pre><code>ggplot(region.caput2, aes(Year, Emission/Population)) + geom_line(aes(group = Region), size=2) +          scale_fill_manual(colour = c("#E41A1C", "#377EB8", "#4DAF4A", "#984EA3", "#FF7F00", "#FFFF33", "#A65628")) </code></pre>  <p>The result is always this: <a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/z3cEt.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/z3cEt.png" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>  <p>Where am I going wrong? Thanks.</p>